content.introtext:
ideation 
[noun]
The process of developing and conveying prescriptive ideas to others, typically in a business setting. It describes the sequence of thoughts - from the original concept to implemention.
content.helptext: Use the arrow buttons on the control panel to move the claw and then press the grab button to try and grab a light bulb to reveal one of the ideas which will be displayed on the scrolling LED panel.

group.userdata: WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #1: A COLLAPSIBLE CARDBOARD VR HEADSET SIX MONTHS BEFORE GOOGLE'S RELEASED THEIR OWN VERSION.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #2: A PAPER-BASED TEST IN TOOTHPASTE ADVERT IN MAGAZINE FOR CHECKING YOUR ORAL HEALTH.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #3: USING 3D DEPTH CAMERAS IN IN-STORE MIRRORS FOR MEASURING THE CUSTOMER'S FACE FOR BETTER FITTING GLASSES.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #4: USING BLUETOOTH LOYALTY CARDS FOR PERSONALISATION & TRACKING INSTORE ACTIVITY OF CUSTOMERS.

WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #5: A POLARISED FILM ON NEW GLASSES SO WHEN CUSTOMERS TRY THEM ON FOR THE FIRST TIME INSTORE, THEY CAN SEE IMAGES ON LCD SCREENS WITH THEIR POLARISED LAYERS REMOVED ELSE THESE SCREENS ARE SEEN AS WHITE LIGHT WITH THE NAKED EYE.

WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #6: USING FACEBOOK'S MESSENGER APP TO ALLOW INSTORE IKEA CUSTOMERS TO TAKE PHOTOS OF THE PRODUCT LABLES IN THE SHOWROOM & BUY THEM INSTANTLY READY FOR COLLECTION WITHOUT QUEUING.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #7: AN ACCELEROMETER INSOLE PLACED IN A SPORTS SHOE TO SHOW RELEVANT INFORMATION ON A DIGITAL DISPLAY BASED ON THE ORIENATION OF THE SHOE.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #8: A POP-UP AR/VR CHILDREN'S BOOK WITH ITS OWN COLLAPSIBLE CARDBOARD AR/VR CHARACTER MASK.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #9: AN AUTOMATON WIMBLEDON TENNIS STATUE FOR ROBINSONS THAT CHANGES ITS POSE (HEAD-IN-HANDS TO PUNCHING THE AIR) TO REFLECT THE MOOD OF THE NATION VIA SOCIAL MEDIA.

WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #10: A 'WILL IT FIT?' APP FOR FORD WHICH WILL TELL YOU WHETHER A PARTICLE ITEM WILL FIT IN YOUR VEHICLE AS WELL AS A PACKING ALGORITHM TO HELP PACK YOUR VEHICLE MORE EFFICIENTLY.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #11: A SMART TASK LAMP USING A CAMERA TO DETERMINE WHAT TASK YOU ARE DOING & AUTOMATICALLY CHANGING THE LEVEL OF LIGHT ACCORDINGLY.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #12: A DIGITAL CHRISTMAS CAMPAIGN FOR A FASHION BRAND ABOUT THE DUALITY OF CHRISTMAS, SPENDING THE DAY WITH YOUR FAMILY & PARTYING IN THE EVENING.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED LUCKY IDEA #13: A EPISODIC MOBILE GAME TO LAUNCH MCDONALDS' HAPPY MEAL MASCOT IN WHICH YOU MUST CONTROL HAPPY TO MAKE THE OTHER CHARACTERS LAUGH.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #14: A POP-UP PAVILION FOR THE LAUNCH OF A NEW SHOPPING CENTRE WITH A USER-GENERATED KALEIDOSCOPE PROJECTION & ASSOCIATED APP.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #15: A PROMOTIONAL POP-UP AR CARDBOARD CUBE THAT CAN BE SENT THROUGH THE POST.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #16: USING COMPUTER VISION & MACHINE LEARNING VIA AN APP TO DETECT THE EARLY ONSET OF GUM DISEASE BY DETECTING GUM RECESSION.

WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #17: AN IN-THE-PUB DIGITAL EXPERIENCE FOR GUINNESS USING SPECIAL GLASSES ENGRAVED WITH CONDUCTIVE METAL ON THEIR BOTTOMS SO ARE RECOGNISED WHEN PLACED ON A TABLET TO ALLOW THE DRINK TO SETTLE.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #18: AN ONLINE AR & VR EXPERIENCE USING CHATBOTS FOR TEACHING ENGLISH AS A FOREIGN LANGUAGE.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #19: A MODULAR-BASED SYSTEM THAT WOULD ALLOW FORD TRANSIT OWNERS TO USE IKEA FURNITURE PARTS TO CUSTOMISE THE VAN INTERIOR FOR THEIR SPECIFIC NEEDS.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #20: A FORD TRANSIT SUN-VISOR CONSISTING OF A SAD LAMP TO ALLOW THE DRIVER TO RE-ENERGISE AFTER A LONG JOURNEY.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #21: A PROMOTIONAL CARDBOARD PROJECTOR FOR A SHOPPING CENTRE LAUNCH THAT ALLOWS CUSTOMERS TO PROJECT THEIR KALEIDOSCOPE CREATIONS ON TO THEIR WALLS AT HOME.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #22: A SWITCHABLE DISPLAY ALCOVE FOR A POP-UP WHICH CONSISTS OF A ONE WAY MIRROR TO ALLOW AN APP TO SWITCH BETWEEN PRODUCTS BASED ON A CUSTOMERS INTEREST.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #23: AN ALCOVE IN A POP-UP WHICH USES PEPPERS GHOST TO ALLOW DIGITAL CONTENT TO BE AUGMENTED OVER A PHYSICAL PRODUCT.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #24: AN IN-PRINT CAMPAIGN FOR A FASHION RETAILER USING A CHILDS' ORIGAMI FORTUNE TELLER TO SELECT CHRISTMAS GIFTS.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #25: AN ONLINE GIFT SELECTOR USING AN ANALOGUE SLIDER TO SHOW HOW MUCH YOU LIKE ONE PRODUCT OVER ANOTHER BY HOW MUCH YOU MOVE THE SLIDER FROM RIGHT TO LEFT.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #26: AN APP FOR TRACKING THE SUGAR CONTENT AND PH LEVELS OF THE FOOD & DRINK YOU CONSUME TO MINIMISE YOUR RISK OF TOOTH DECAY.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #27: AN ATTACHMENT FOR YOUR PHONE TO ALLOW YOU TO TAKE A PHOTO OF THE INSIDE OF YOUR MOUTH WHICH CAN BE SENT TO A DENTIST FOR ASSESSMENT.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #28: A 'SIRI FOR KIDS' CONCEPT FOR MCDONALDS USING AN INTERACTIVE VOICE-ACTIVATED APP.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #29: A SERIES OF BEER MATS FOR GUINNESS TO BRING TO LIFE THEIR HERITAGE BRANDED CHARACTERS VIA AR.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #30: AN APP FOR EXCERCISING THE MUSCLES IN YOUR EYES TO IMPROVE YOUR EYESIGHT.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #31: USING CONDUCTIVE INK MAKE MCDONALDS' HAPPY MEAL BOX INTERACTIVE WITH CUP ACTING AS THE SPEAKER.
WELL DONE YOU'VE GRABBED IDEA #32: USE THE MCDONALDS' TRAY AS THE INPUT DEVICE USING THE PHONE'S IN-BUILT GYROSCOPE TO PICK-UP THE VIBRATIONS AS YOU TAP THE TRAY.

meshlabel.text: USE THE BUTTONS TO MOVE THE CLAW TO GRAB AN IDEA. GOOD LUCK!

content.introtext:
problem-solving 
[noun]
The process of finding solutions to difficult or complex issues.
content.helptext: Tilt the cube to move the balls around the maze, down the slope, through the gates, up the ferris wheel and load them into the cannon to fire them at the targets.

content.introtext:
interview 
[noun]
A formal meeting at which someone is asked a series of questions in order to find out if they are suitable for a job.
content.helptext:
My avatar is well-versed in answering some of those typical interview questions like 'why do you want to work here?' or 'what will you bring to the role?'.
Press the mic button on the screen and ask them a question to hear the reply.

content.introtext:
teamworking 
[noun]
The ability of a group of people to work well together given their individual tasks and roles with the aim of achieving a common goal.
content.helptext: Click on the highlighted arrows to move the characters around to enable the top character to reach the top platform and ring the bell.

content.introtext:
innovative 
[adjective]
Someone who introduces new ideas; original and creative thinking.
content.helptext: Move Kester into the rocket by clicking on the arrows and then withdraw the ladder, close the door and launch the rocket by pressing the numbered buttons on the control panel when prompted.

content.introtext:
multifaceted 
[adjective]
A person who has many different talents in all kinds of fields and subject areas.
content.helptext: Click on the direction arrows to move the Kesters up and down the stairs, and click on the Kesters who are engaged in activities to find out what they are doing.

texttospeech.text: Hi. I'm just finishing off this painting. Did you know I can draw and paint and even studied fine art as my first degree? If you don't mind, I'll get back to painting. Thanks
Hi. I can programme in a variety of different languages and on a variety of different platforms.
Hey there! I can design and use packages such as Photoshop.
Hello. I can build physical prototypes using cardboard and physical computing using Arduinos too.
Hey there! I can also pitch and present ideas to clients and fellow team members.
Hello. I'm just listening to this very engaging pitch.
Hello. I can come up with creative concepts either individually or working in a team.
Hi. I can brainstorm with others to come up with creative ideas and strategies.
